5 B. When any vehicle making use of any visual signals as authorized by law,
6 including the display of alternately flashing green, amber, or yellow warning lights,
7 as defined by R.S. 32:1(110), is parked on or near the highway, disabled,
8 immobilized, nonoperational or is making use of any visual signals including the
9 display of flashing lights, hazard lamps, or any emergency warning devices, the
10 driver of every other passing or approaching vehicle shall:
11 (1) When driving on an interstate highway or other highway with two or
12 more lanes traveling in the same direction, yield the right-of-way when driving on
13 an interstate highway or other highway with two or more lanes traveling in the
14 same direction, by making a lane change into a lane not adjacent to the parked
15 vehicle, if possible with due regard to safety and traffic conditions. If a lane change
16 is not possible, unsafe, or driving on a two-lane road or highway, the driver shall
17 slow to a reasonably safe speed and maintain a safe speed for road conditions.
18 (2) Maintain a safe speed for road conditions, if unable or unsafe to change
19 lanes, or driving on a two-lane road or highway.
20 C. This Section shall not operate to relieve the driver of an authorized
21 emergency vehicle from the duty to drive with due regard for the safety of all
22 persons using the highway.
23 D. Any person who violates the provisions of this Section shall, upon
24 conviction, be subject to a fine not to exceed two hundred dollars.
25 D. The Department of Public Safety and Corrections shall promulgate
26 rules pursuant to this Section.
